article.headline: Virginia Tech 73, Radford 60
article.story: BLACKSBURG, Va. (AP) -- Bryant Matthews and Zabian Dowdell scored 18 points apiece Saturday night, leading Virginia Tech to a 73-60 victory against Radford. The Hokies (5-3) led 31-22 at halftime and by at least seven throughout the second half, with Matthews scoring 16 points after the break and Coleman Collins 11. Radford (4-4) was led by Chris Goodin with 15 points. The Highlanders shot just 32 percent from the field and turned the ball over 15 times, leading to 18 Hokies points. As they had in their 80-56 victory against VMI earlier in the week, the Hokies took command with a sizeable first-half run. Against the Keydets, it was 21 consecutive points. Against the Highlanders, it was 15, giving Tech a 24-9 lead with 8:55 to play. Collins, a freshman playing his first game, had 15 points and seven rebounds, and Jamon Gordon and Markus Sailes each scored nine. Gordon also has six assists. Whit Holcomb-Faye and Chris Oliver each scored 10 for Radford.
